(106,	0,	1,	20240816,	'ask',	'how can I migrate to Australia?',	1,	0,	'2024-08-16 14:11:44',	0,	'2024-08-16 14:11:44',	0,	NULL),
(107,	106,	1,	20240816,	'reply',	'**Eligibility Criteria:**\n\n* **Age:** Generally, applicants must be under 45 years of age for most skilled visas.\n* **Occupation:** Your occupation must be in demand in Australia and listed on the Skilled Occupation List (SOL).\n* **Work Experience:** Typically, you need relevant work experience in your nominated occupation.\n* **Education:** You may need a relevant qualification or educational assessment.\n* **English Proficiency:** You must demonstrate proficient English language skills through an accredited test (e.g., IELTS, TOEFL).\n* **Health and Character:** You must meet health and character requirements.\n\n**Step-by-Step Guide:**\n\n**1. Determine Your Eligibility:**\n* Check your occupation on the SOL.\n* Assess your work experience and educational qualifications.\n* Prepare your English language test results.\n\n**2. Create an Expression of Interest (EOI) Profile:**\n* Register for an ImmiAccount and submit an EOI through SkillSelect.\n* Provide information about your skills, education, work experience, and language abilities.\n\n**3. Skill Assessment (If Required):**\n* For some occupations, you may need your skills assessed by a designated assessing authority.\n\n**4. Apply for a Visa:**\n* If your EOI is selected, you will be invited to apply for a visa.\n* Choose the appropriate visa subclass based on your circumstances.\n* Submit a complete visa application, including all supporting documents.\n\n**5. Visa Processing:**\n* Your visa application will be assessed by the Australian Department of Home Affairs.\n* Processing times vary and can be several months.\n\n**6. Medical and Police Checks:**\n* You may be required to undergo medical and police checks.\n\n**7. Visa Grant:**\n* If your visa is approved, you will receive a visa grant letter.\n\n**8. Prepare for Your Arrival:**\n* Book flights, arrange accommodation, and inform relevant parties about your relocation.\n\n**Additional Considerations:**\n\n* **State Nomination:** Some states and territories have their own skilled migration programs and may offer additional points or support.\n* **Family Sponsorship:** You may be able to migrate through family sponsorship if you have a family member who is an Australian citizen or permanent resident.\n* **Employer Sponsorship:** If you have a job offer in Australia, your employer may be able to sponsor your visa.\n* **Fees:** Visa application fees and other related costs apply.\n* **Professional Assistance:** You may consider using a migration agent to assist you with the process.\n\n**Resources:**\n\n* SkillSelect: https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/skillselect\n* Australian Government Department of Home Affairs: https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au\n* Skilled Occupation List (SOL): https://immi.homeaffairs.gov.au/visas/working-in-australia/skill-occupation-list',	1,	0,	'2024-08-16 14:11:44',	0,	'2024-08-16 14:11:44',	0,	NULL),
